article.description: Ioannis Dimakopoulos scored 15 points and UC Irvine snapped a three-game slide, rolling past UC Santa Barbara 64-47 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: UC Irvine rolls past UC Santa Barbara 64-47
article.linkText: UC Irvine rolls past UC Santa Barbara 64-47
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. -- Ioannis Dimakopoulos scored 15 points and UC Irvine snapped a three-game slide, rolling past UC Santa Barbara 64-47 on Wednesday night. Dimakopoulos was 6 of 7 from the floor for the Anteaters (14-12, 7-3 Big West). Luke Nelson added 11 points and Jonathan Galloway netted a double-double with 10 points and 10 rebounds. The team averaged 41.7 percent shooting from the floor -- compared to 34.5 percent for UCSB -- and had a 46-30 rebounding edge over the Gauchos (3-19, 1-9). UC Irvine led early and never trailed on its way to a 27-18 advantage at the break. Nelson drained a 3-pointer midway through the second half, Galloway followed with a three-point play and Dimakopoulos and Tommy Rutherford each hit a layup to stretch the Anteaters' lead to 48-31 with 9:03 to go. They cruised from there. Alex Hart scored 16 points for the Gauchos who are on a seven-game skid.
